name: Mackerel and horse mackerel eggs
description: The survey existed since 1968. It is carried out every 3 years in thenorth eastern Atlantic. The year after the Atlantic survey, a mackerel egg surveyis conducted in theNorth Sea. The survey createsa basis for thestock assessment of Atlantic and North Sea mackerel andmanagement plan for Atlantic horse mackerel. The historical MEGS data is expected to be uploaded in 2015-2016.The group responsible forthe survey is WGMEGS.
